# Jira Dashboard — Environment Variables
#
# Secrets are now loaded from AWS Secrets Manager at startup.
# .env is no longer used for secrets — do not create a local .env file.
#
# The app authenticates to AWS using:
#   - Local dev: ~/.aws/credentials (run `aws configure` or use AWS SSO)
#   - Production: IAM role attached to the EC2/ECS/Lambda instance
#
# ── Secrets Manager config (override if needed) ────────────────────────────────
# AWS_SECRET_NAME=mwambsganss/jira-dashboard   # name of the secret in Secrets Manager
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1                          # region where the secret lives
#
# ── Secrets stored in AWS Secrets Manager (mwambsganss/jira-dashboard) ────────
# The secret must be a JSON object with these keys:
#
#   SSO_TENANT_ID           — Lilly Azure AD tenant ID
#   SSO_CLIENT_ID           — Azure AD app client ID
#   SSO_CLIENT_SECRET       — Azure AD app client secret
#   SECRET_KEY              — random string for encrypting stored credentials at rest
#   LLM_KEY                 — (optional) static bearer token for LLM gateway
#   LLM_URL                 — https://lilly-code-server.api.gateway.llm.lilly.com
#   LLM_CLIENT_ID           — (optional) client ID for LLM OAuth2 client-credentials flow
#   LLM_CLIENT_SECRET       — (optional) client secret for LLM OAuth2 flow
#   LLM_TENANT_ID           — (optional) tenant ID for LLM OAuth2 flow
#   LLM_SCOPE               — (optional) OAuth2 scope (default: https://cognitiveservices.azure.com/.default)
#   SMTP_RELAY_HOST         — (optional) SMTP relay host (default: smtp-z1-nomx.lilly.com)
#   SMTP_RELAY_PORT         — (optional) SMTP relay port (default: 25)
#   PORT                    — (optional) server port, default 5002
